title: R&A Cycles New York City Cycling Series
Regional Orthopedics Tuesday Night Race Series
the Women's Woodstock Cycling Grand Prix
description: The event is  comprised of 3 separate Women races run on the same course, except for two races the distance to finish is shortened by taking a more direct route to finish line.
course: An out and back course consisting of flat and hilly roads, with 3 substantial ascents with an average gradient of 10%. Note: on Mead;s Mtn. Road, there is a 19% grade section.) Included on the course for all 3 races is a 1 mile dirt-road section.
registration: Registration is either PRE-Register by bikereg.com, or day of, opening at 6:30 am at the Woodstock Day School, Glasco Turnpike. A $10 late fee will be added to the cost of registration. Day-of-race licenses will be available.
notes: This is a course for those athlete\'s seeking to test thier over bike racing skills, climbing. descending, dealing with side winds. The road surface for most of the course is excellent, but it is recommended to use heavy duty wheels and tires.
directions: Take the New York State Thruway to the Saugerties exit, and take Rte. 212 towards Woodstock for approx. 6 miles and then look for Glasco Turnpike and race signage. Mandatory parking at the Woodstock Jewish Congregation. Note: the OFFICIAL start point is 1/4 of a mile away on Glasco Turnpike at the Woodstock Day School.

title: Yorktown Cycles Kids Mountain Bike Day
Kreb Cycle Friday Nights
description: Kreb Cycle Friday night races are a weekly (with some breaks) racing series held at Suffolk Community College in Riverhead NY. The series has been active for 30+ years. We have different events through out the summer. Circuit races, Win and Out, Points race, Individual Time Trials, and a Team Time Trial.
course: The course is on Ring Road, the road the makes the the outer boundary of the college. There are no sharp turns and no major climbs. It's basically an oval. The course is closed to traffic but occasionally a car does get on the course.
registration: Registration is on Bike Reg or the day of the race. We have 3 fields. Cat 1-4, Cat 4,5 and Cat 5 one day. We will have 2 dates that replace the Cat 4,5 race with a women's only field. Registration opens @ 5:30 and close @ 6:00. Racing starts at 6:15. All three races are on the course at the same time, the fields have a 1 min separation at the start. Please keep your number for the summer!!!
notes: This race is a training race. We don't use any fancy timing equipment and we don't give out allot of prize money. The idea is to provide a place for people who are looking for a race to have that chance on eastern Long Island. If you need us to tell you if you got 8th or 9th place in a race this might not be the race for you. If you want to try out a different sprinting tactic, take a flyer with 2 to go or lead out a friend you might like our races. We do race in the rain but lightning will cancel the event. If it's pouring out and 6 knuckle heads show up I'm not going to stand out there with the lap cards getting soaked. If 10 of you show up I might. If we cancel the race and you preregistered you'll get a free entry in another race. Most importantly race safely. We all need to got to work on Monday (I'll be working bright and early the next morning thank you), so please don't pretend this is the Tour De France, or even Somerville! We would like to see you next week. Lets keep it real.
directions: Suffolk Community College in Riverhead. The college is on Riverhead Speonk Road. Take CR51 to the signs for the college. You can take the LIE to rte 111 to get to CR 51, or Sunrise Hwy to directly to the CR 51 exit. Take 51 north to Riverhead.

title: ESC NYS Championship Super D at Plattekill Mountai
description:
Races Starts will be LeMans style mass starts by racer class.
Racers will be given a start signal and run to their bikes, first one to the bottom wins. No timing but lots of fun racing side by side.
course:
Tracks will be enduro style, mostly downhill with some flat pedal sprints and possibly some short uphill sections. Downhill bikes will battle trail bikes in these races.

Course cutting by leaving the obvious trail will result in disqualification
Racers being passed should yield when it is be safe to do so.
Helmets must be worn at all times on venues property while riding a bicycle.
Only one bike may be used per event.
Any age may race in the Pro open Class,
Any age may race in a younger class except for 19-29 racers.
Women can race in women’s classes or age groups.
registration:
ESC Super D races are permitted by USA Cycling.
An annual or day license is required to race.
Day Licenses are available at all enduro races for $5.
Day licenses allow racers to race any Class including the Pro/Open due to the “Open” format
(This does not apply to the ESC DH Series. The DH Series does not offer the “Pro/Open format”)

title: 49th Annual Kissena Labor Day Track Meet
NYCROSS Clinic
description:
Great clinic for first timer cross racers!  The clinic will cover a wide range of skills and topics needed for cross racing including:

- Proper technique for:
   - rapidly dismounting your bike at barriers
   - remounting your bike
   - shouldering your bike at run ups
   - high speed cornering on grass, mud and other surfaces
   - sand pits
   - short steep hills
   - long, lung busting run ups
- Training methods for cross including:
   - skill building drills
   - weekly workout regimines for building speed on a cross course
   - mental preparation and race tactics
   - warming up for a cross race
   - proper nutrition and hydration while racing cross
- Bike set up:
   - Tubulars vs. Clinchers
   - How many gears?
   - light vs. strong. vs cheap parts
   - fit suggestions
course: Clinic will include stations teaching basic cross skills and a short course for participants to apply there newly learned skills
registration:
www.bikereg.com/nycrosscom-cyclocross-clinic

Registration is $25
notes: The clinic will run from 10:00 am until 1pm and be divided into a short question and answer period, drills developing individual cross skills, a short mock race where students will have the opportunity to link the individual skills they've learned together on a short cross course, and a final Q&A period.
directions:
Directions:

Travel East on RT 7 to Troy, entering Troy, make a right onto Eighth Street at the light at the end of the RT 7 Bridge. Follow Eighth Street to its end and make a left onto Congress Street. Prospect Park is on your right, .3 miles after the intersection of Eighth and Congress.
- From the West: RT 7 east to Troy, follow directions above.

Stay on RT 2/Congress St, Prospect Park is on your left, .5 miles from the intersection of RT 2 and Pawling Ave.
